®The FerrymanŌĆÖs Seat

The FerrymanŌĆÖs seat, located on the previous building at this site, was constructed for the convenience of Bankside
watermen, who operated ferrying services across the river.
The seatŌĆÖs age is unknown, but it is thought to have ancient origins.

